Virginia Tech, known for its Electronic Village, was rocked by a tragic shooting.
The university, with 25,000 students, is a hub for research in various fields.
The campus faced a horrific attack, leaving 32 dead and many injured.
Questions arose about the response to the shootings.
President Bush expressed horror and attended a memorial service.
The gunman's identity and motive are under investigation.
This incident, the deadliest in US history, has led to the cancellation of classes for the week.
The nation mourns the senseless loss of life at Virginia Tech.
